our sex!

17:19.965 --> 17:21.206
- Well!

17:21.275 --> 17:22.862
How is it with Charles?

17:22.931 --> 17:24.275
- Oh, don't get me wrong.

17:24.344 --> 17:26.241
It is really hot
with Charles too.

17:26.310 --> 17:29.172
- They bring out
different things in you.

17:29.241 --> 17:31.241
Why not just have both?
- Oh!

17:31.310 --> 17:33.827
but it doesn't work that way,
Nurse Maureen.

17:33.896 --> 17:35.413
I can't do that!

17:35.482 --> 17:37.103
- But can you do this?

17:44.000 --> 17:45.896
Yeah!
- Wow!

17:45.965 --> 17:47.241
I can't do that.

17:47.310 --> 17:49.137
- I bet you can!

17:56.310 --> 17:58.275
-  Whoa...

17:58.344 --> 17:59.896
I'm amazing!

17:59.965 --> 18:01.482
Ohh...ohh!

18:01.551 --> 18:04.000
- Look at you go!
- Oh!

18:39.827 --> 18:41.586
- ♪ Hey ♪

18:41.655 --> 18:43.620
♪ Hey ♪

18:43.689 --> 18:44.793
♪ Hey ♪

19:20.517 --> 19:22.310
- Yep.

19:22.379 --> 19:24.241
Super-taster.

19:30.413 --> 19:31.931
- You sure
you're okay?

19:32.000 --> 19:33.620
I burn bright,

19:33.689 --> 19:35.655
but I fade faster.

19:35.724 --> 19:37.965
- You know, I had
a really, uh,

19:38.034 --> 19:40.379
interesting conversation
with Josh.

19:40.448 --> 19:43.034
- Oh, really?
- Yeah, it's, uh,

19:43.103 --> 19:45.172
it's nice to see him
start a family.

19:45.241 --> 19:47.965
Makes me think about

19:48.034 --> 19:50.068
how important
family is to me.

19:50.137 --> 19:52.068
- For both of us.

19:52.137 --> 19:54.103
- You know,
I think this weekend

19:54.172 --> 19:56.206
really did expand
my mind...

19:57.586 --> 20:00.172
- In ways I wasn't
expecting.

20:00.241 --> 20:02.689
- You sure
you're okay to drive?

20:02.758 --> 20:05.379
- Yeah. Come on.

20:14.655 --> 20:16.241
- Hey.

20:16.310 --> 20:17.965
How was your weekend?

20:18.034 --> 20:21.448
- Well, I got hog-tied
in my painting harness.

20:21.517 --> 20:23.413
- Wh--
- And the guy that lives

20:23.482 --> 20:24.689
across the street
watched me

20:24.758 --> 20:26.482
while he jerked off
to it.

20:26.551 --> 20:28.034
- Oh, my God!
That is awful.

20:28.103 --> 20:29.965
Are you okay?
- Am I okay?

20:30.034 --> 20:33.344
I'm great.
I got my mojo back.

20:39.931 --> 20:42.206
-  And how was
your drug escapade?

20:42.275 --> 20:43.827
- Oh, do you have a cold?

20:43.896 --> 20:46.758
I have a lozenge in my purse.
- No, I'm--

20:46.827 --> 20:48.241
Don't you find it sexy?

20:48.310 --> 20:50.689
A lot of people
find it sexy.

20:50.758 --> 20:51.793
- Oh!

20:52.758 --> 20:53.827
Yes.

20:53.896 --> 20:56.103
- Never mind.
Just--where's my plant?

20:56.172 --> 20:57.862
- What?
- You kept sending me photos

20:57.931 --> 21:01.482
of a plant--I just assumed
it was a gift for me.

21:03.068 --> 21:05.000
- Maureen.

21:05.068 --> 21:06.379
- Hey,
did you get the book?

21:06.448 --> 21:07.793
- We don't know,

21:07.862 --> 21:09.827
but we got something
even better.

21:09.896 --> 21:11.103
- What?

21:11.172 --> 21:12.965
- Charles wants to
tell you himself.

21:15.551 --> 21:19.068
- Mercury's success has
started to hurt my family,

21:19.137 --> 21:21.862
which is...all of you.

21:21.931 --> 21:23.896
And it is time

21:23.965 --> 21:26.517
to let that go.

21:27.862 --> 21:30.586
- You're closing up Mercury.

21:30.655 --> 21:32.379
- I want you to buy it.

21:32.448 --> 21:35.172
- We'd love to, Charles,
but...

21:35.241 --> 21:37.793
we can't afford it.

21:46.965 --> 21:48.758
- Here's how much I want.

21:50.482 --> 21:52.827
Million dollars.

21:54.275 --> 21:56.482
We don't have
a million dollars.

21:56.551 --> 21:58.482
- I don't see any zeros.

21:58.551 --> 22:01.310
- $1.

22:01.379 --> 22:03.517
My grandfather mortgaged

22:03.586 --> 22:05.655
everything to start this place.

22:05.724 --> 22:08.620
He was doing something
to keep his family together,

22:08.689 --> 22:12.000
and I am tired
of fighting with mine.

22:13.413 --> 22:16.206
I want to come home.

22:16.275 --> 22:18.206
- As publisher.

22:18.275 --> 22:20.172
- If I come back,
it would be as an editor.

22:20.241 --> 22:23.862
An editor whose relationship
with a fellow editor

22:23.931 --> 22:26.068
is nobody's business.

22:26.137 --> 22:30.172
You would be publisher, Kelsey.
I would be working for you.

22:30.241 --> 22:31.689
Next to Liza.

22:33.068 --> 22:35.758
On those terms, uh,

22:35.827 --> 22:37.482
I say yes.

22:38.586 --> 22:40.379
Ladies?
- I say yes.

22:40.448 --> 22:41.862
- Oh, I absolutely
say yes.

22:41.931 --> 22:44.137
I'll give you a fiver.
You can keep the change.

22:44.206 --> 22:47.241
-  Thank you.

22:47.310 --> 22:49.413
I think we'll be stronger
together.

22:49.482 --> 22:51.827
- Welcome home, Charles.

